hopobject.body: What's the interest rate on this account? powerhealthreno.com A group of companies with billion-dollar valuations on theprivate market will be watching closely. Box Chief ExecutiveOfficer Aaron Levie said earlier this year that his business-software company will likely go public in 2014. Airbnb, operatorof a home-rental website, was valued at $2.5 billion last year.Square, the payments startup run by Twitter co-founder Jack Dorsey, achieved a valuation of $3.25 billion a year ago afteran investment from Starbucks Corp., while document storageprovider Dropbox was valued at $4 billion in a 2011 financing.
